# Keeps the Docker build context small and the layer cache useful — see
# infra/README.md. Only `infra/*/Dockerfile` builds happen in this repo
# today (the bootstrap-node `daemon` binary and `bh-push-relay`), both of
# which need the Cargo workspace (workspace-relative paths in Cargo.toml
# mean every crate under `crates/`, plus `daemon/` and
# `client/desktop/src-tauri/` since they're workspace members, has to stay
# in the build context even though the Tauri crate itself isn't built by
# either infra image) but never the desktop client's own build output or
# any local Rust build cache.
target/
client/desktop/node_modules/
client/desktop/dist/
client/desktop/src-tauri/target/
.git/
docs/
*.md
